cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.ST, cs.SI, cs.CL 

The paper presents a novel algorithm for clustering batch-sequential data containing an unknown number of evolving clusters. This falls under the domain of machine learning and data mining, which is covered by several sub-categories in arXiv CS. The use of probabilistic models and empirical evaluation suggests that cs.LG (Machine Learning) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also involves the use of algorithms and statistical analysis, which could place it under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.ST (Statistics). The use of real-world data from aircraft trajectory suggests that cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) could also be a relevant sub-category. Finally, the paper involves clustering, which is a common topic in cs.CL (Computation and Language).
